body:
Hi

We will be having a general meetup regarding the activities of PyJaipur.

- 11:00 - 14:00 hrs on Jan 5 2020.
- [Venue is Forsk labs, Sitapura, Jaipur](https://g.page/forsklabs?share)

## Agenda

- ~[ ] Clear backlog from previous events~ Could not be discussed due to absent members
- [x] Promotional links and a bot for them
- [x] Monthly meetup schedule
- [x] Talks schedule
- [x] Projects / Sponsorship / Activities

Please react to this comment with a rocket emoji to indicate your presence :rocket: 

## Attended
@theSage21, @rishabhKalakoti, @anchal7299, Surender, Sylvester

## Discussed and finalized:

1. Monthly meetups will be held regularly. Bi-weekly local member meetups will be remote/online
2. PyJaipur's participation in CodeNBuild might be questionable since our role there is not clear. See #9 for event details.
3. Community learning tracks need to be finalized. Potential candidates
    - Web development
    - Data science
4. Calculate group churn
5. Open source projects built by the PyJaipur community. Perhaps contribute to other communities (https://github.com/pythonindia/junction is a good candidate)

comment_data.body: Let's just use the rocket emoji to mean that someone will be attending.

Let's assemble at Forsk labs in Sitapura. They've been supportive of PyJaipur so far and it would be nice to start the new year with them :smile: 

https://g.page/forsklabs?share
Timings available for us are 1100 hrs to 1400 hrs. Please be in the venue at 1100 hrs. I'll meet everyone there.
I'll see you all at 11 AM tomorrow :smile:

Attended: @theSage21, @rishabhKalakoti, @anchal7299, Surender, Sylvester

Discussed and finalized:

1. Monthly meetups will be held regularly. Bi-weekly local member meetups will be remote/online
2. PyJaipur's participation in CodeNBuild might be questionable since our role there is not clear. See #9 for event details.
3. Community learning tracks need to be finalized. Potential candidates

5. Open source projects built by the PyJaipur community. Perhaps contribute to other communities (https://github.com/pythonindia/junction is a good candidate)

Please let me know if I missed something.
